
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `foo2hiperc` yek driver baraye printer-haye GDI (Graphics Device Interface) ast, be vizhe printer-haye rangie arzan gheimat. In driver eejad mikonad format-haye file raster-based ke ba in printer-ha sazgar hastand.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 Hich gozine-ye mostaghim dar command line nist. `foo2hiperc` obiatan be onvane yek filter estefade mishavad, masalan az taraf CUPS (Common Unix Printing System).
    🔹 Configuration obiatan az tarighe system-haye chap (printing) mesle CUPS anjam mishavad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    Az aanja ke `foo2hiperc` be tor mostaghim az command line estefade nemishavad, mesal-e mostaghim baraye ejra-ye aan nist.

    Ama dar configuration CUPS, mitoonid printer ra ba `foo2hiperc` set konid.

    $ # Dar CUPS GUI ya az tarighe file configuration
    $ # Driver: foo2hiperc

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    Tasavvor konid yek file PDF dar CUPS chap mikonid. CUPS az `foo2hiperc` estefade mikonad ta data PDF ra be format-i ke printer shoma mitoonad chap konad tabdil konad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `foo2hiperc` command is a printer driver for GDI (Graphics Device Interface) printers, especially low-cost color printers. It generates raster-based file formats compatible with these printers.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 There are no direct command-line options. `foo2hiperc` is typically used as a filter, for example, by CUPS (Common Unix Printing System).
    🔹 Configuration is usually done through printing systems like CUPS.

🛠 **Examples:**

    Since `foo2hiperc` isn't directly used from the command line, there are no direct execution examples.

    However, in a CUPS configuration, you can set up a printer using `foo2hiperc`.

    $ # In CUPS GUI or via configuration file
    $ # Driver: foo2hiperc

✅ **Simple Example:**

    Imagine printing a PDF file in CUPS. CUPS uses `foo2hiperc` to translate the PDF data into a format that your printer can print.
